    "Multiple recurrent Clostridioides difficile infected patients were treated with faecal microbiota transplantation in 34 different centres across the Netherlands and samples were requested for research.",
    "Only patients are included in the analyses if we received both a pre-and post-FMT sample Fig. 22Fig.",
    "2 Effect of faecal microbiota transplantation on prevalence and abundance of cultured multidrug resistant bacteria.",
    "Stool samples of recurrent C. difficile infected (rCDI) patients were selectively cultured to assess the prevalence of multidrug-resistant (MDR) bacteria before and after faecal microbiota transplantation (FMT).",
    "We called samples MDR positive if at least one MDR bacterium was detected."
